Rating: 4
I boiled the crab shells in the broth for about 1 hour. This added more crab flavor to the broth. I also used Madeira instead of Sherry, and everyone loved this soup! It turned out amazing.

Rating: 3
I usually hate it when people review a recipe and say they loved it but changed it a lot. Well I was drawn to this recipe because I love crab and mushrooms. But after looking at some other crab bisque recipes felt it needed to be tweaked. I followed all the ingredients of the recipe but added a tablespoon of tomatoe paste and instead of straining the mixture and discarding the solid I put the mixture in the blender. I also added some thyme. Also my mushrooms didn't have long stems so I put about 1/2 of the mushrooms in the first soup mixture and only used 4 or 5 for the garnish. I loved the result.

Rating: 2
After reading earlier reviews, I chose the mildest white mushrooms and just used half. After adding a bit more sherry and a teaspoon of cognac at the end, we had a fairly tasty mushroom bisque with crab bits. There was no hint of seafood taste. Not surprising in retrospect. Chicken stock plus mushrooms doesn't make crab bisque.

Rating: 2
